{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775861456698,"sessionID":"ses_2866926a4ffeNtgxusNCl20XGx","part":{"id":"prt_d7996f978001Vpf1I6AGcdZXyi","messageID":"msg_d7996e9f3001pw9MamNsqaSqzK","sessionID":"ses_2866926a4ffeNtgxusNCl20XGx","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_5df7dc9800a44aea98d06d24","state":{"status":"error","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/design.md","content":"# AR-017: PicoD JWT Middleware - Technical Design\n\n## Architecture\n\n### Overview\nJWT middleware for PicoD HTTP server that validates JWT tokens on incoming requests. The middleware sits in the HTTP handler chain and intercepts requests to protected endpoints.\n\n```\n┌─────────────┐     ┌──────────────┐     ┌─────────────┐     ┌─────────────┐\n│   Client    │────▶│  PicoD HTTP  │────▶│ JWT Middle- │────▶│   Handler   │\n│  (with JWT) │     │   Server     │     │   ware      │     │  (Business) │\n└─────────────┘     └──────────────┘     └─────────────┘     └─────────────┘\n```\n\n### Package Structure\n```\npkg/picod/\n├── jwt/\n│   ├── middleware.go      # HTTP middleware handler\n│   ├── validator.go       # JWT validation logic\n│   ├── claims.go          # Custom claims structure\n│   ├── config.go          # Configuration types\n│   └── error.go           # Error types\n├── server.go              # PicoD server integration\n└── ...\n```\n\n## Data Structures\n\n### Config\n```go\ntype Config struct {\n    // SigningKey is the secret key for HMAC verification\n    SigningKey []byte\n    \n    // SigningMethod is the signing algorithm (default: \"HS256\")\n    SigningMethod string\n    \n    // SkipPaths are paths that bypass JWT validation\n    SkipPaths map[string]bool\n    \n    // TokenLookup defines where to extract token from\n    // Format: \"header:<name>\" or \"query:<name>\"\n    TokenLookup string\n    \n    // ContextKey is the key to store claims in context\n    ContextKey string\n}\n```\n\n### Claims\n```go\ntype Claims struct {\n    jwt.RegisteredClaims\n    \n    // Custom claims\n    UserID    string `json:\"user_id,omitempty\"`\n    Namespace string `json:\"namespace,omitempty\"`\n    Roles     []string `json:\"roles,omitempty\"`\n}\n```\n\n### Middleware\n```go\ntype Middleware struct {\n    config   *Config\n    keyFunc  jwt.Keyfunc\n    parser   *jwt.Parser\n}\n```\n\n### Context Keys\n```go\ntype contextKey string\nconst (\n    ClaimsKey contextKey = \"jwt_claims\"\n)\n```\n\n## API Contract\n\n### Middleware Constructor\n```go\nfunc New(config Config) (*Middleware, error)\n```\nReturns configured middleware instance or error if config is invalid.\n\n### HTTP Handler\n```go\nfunc (m *Middleware) Handler(next http.Handler) http.Handler\n```\nWraps next handler with JWT validation logic.\n\n### Context Extraction\n```go\nfunc GetClaims(ctx context.Context) (*Claims, bool)\n```\nExtracts validated claims from request context.\n\n### Error Response\n```go\ntype Error struct {\n    Code    string `json:\"code\"`\n    Message string `json:\"message\"`\n}\n```\n\nStandard error codes:\n- `JWT_MISSING`: No token provided\n- `JWT_INVALID`: Token format/structure invalid\n- `JWT_EXPIRED`: Token has expired\n- `JWT_SIGNATURE_INVALID`: Signature verification failed\n\n## Implementation Flow\n\n1. **Request Interception**\n   - Check if path is in SkipPaths\n   - Extract token from header/query per TokenLookup\n\n2. **Token Validation**\n   - Parse JWT with configured parser\n   - Verify signature using keyFunc\n   - Validate standard claims (exp, nbf, iat)\n   - Custom validation hooks\n\n3. **Context Injection**\n   - Store validated claims in request context\n   - Pass to downstream handler\n\n4. **Error Handling**\n   - Return 401 for auth failures\n   - Return 403 for permission failures\n   - JSON error response body\n\n## Error Handling\n\n### Validation Errors\n```go\nvar (\n    ErrTokenMissing     = errors.New(\"jwt: token missing\")\n    ErrTokenInvalid     = errors.New(\"jwt: token invalid\")\n    ErrTokenExpired     = errors.New(\"jwt: token expired\")\n    ErrSignatureInvalid = errors.New(\"jwt: signature invalid\")\n)\n```\n\n### HTTP Response Codes\n| Scenario | Status | Response Body |\n|----------|--------|---------------|\n| Missing token | 401 | `{\"code\":\"JWT_MISSING\",\"message\":\"Authorization token required\"}` |\n| Invalid format | 401 | `{\"code\":\"JWT_INVALID\",\"message\":\"Invalid token format\"}` |\n| Expired token | 401 | `{\"code\":\"JWT_EXPIRED\",\"message\":\"Token has expired\"}` |\n| Bad signature | 401 | `{\"code\":\"JWT_SIGNATURE_INVALID\",\"message\":\"Invalid token signature\"}` |\n\n## Testing Strategy\n\n### Unit Tests\n```go\n// jwt/validator_test.go\n- TestValidateToken_ValidToken\n- TestValidateToken_ExpiredToken\n- TestValidateToken_InvalidSignature\n- TestValidateToken_MalformedToken\n\n// jwt/middleware_test.go\n- TestMiddleware_SkipPath\n- TestMiddleware_HeaderExtraction\n- TestMiddleware_QueryExtraction\n- TestMiddleware_ContextInjection\n- TestMiddleware_UnauthorizedResponse\n\n// jwt/config_test.go\n- TestNew_InvalidConfig\n- TestNew_DefaultValues\n```\n\n### Integration Tests\n```go\n// jwt/integration_test.go\n- TestFullRequestFlow_WithValidJWT\n- TestFullRequestFlow_WithExpiredJWT\n- TestFullRequestFlow_WithoutJWT\n- TestFullRequestFlow_WithSkipPath\n```\n\n### Test Utilities\n```go\n// jwt/test_helpers.go\n- GenerateTestToken(claims, key, expiry) -> string\n- MockHTTPHandler() -> http.HandlerFunc\n- NewTestRequest(token, path) -> *http.Request\n```\n\n## Dependencies\n\n- `github.com/golang-jwt/jwt/v5` - JWT parsing and validation\n- Standard library: `net/http`, `context`, `errors`\n\n## Security Considerations\n\n1. **Key Management**: SigningKey should be loaded from environment/secret store\n2. **Algorithm Restriction**: Explicitly set allowed signing methods\n3. **Token Expiry**: Enforce reasonable expiry validation (max 24h)\n4. **Path Whitelisting**: Default-deny, only SkipPaths are public\n"},"error":"You must read file /home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/design.md before overwriting it. Use the Read tool first","time":{"start":1775861456685,"end":1775861456695}}}}
