{"type":"text","timestamp":1775861469439,"sessionID":"ses_2866926a4ffeNtgxusNCl20XGx","part":{"id":"prt_d79978da3001KiA5W2Rx5hstuh","messageID":"msg_d79977dbc001HPUkan2NSsP0sm","sessionID":"ses_2866926a4ffeNtgxusNCl20XGx","type":"text","text":"I see the existing `design.md` contains documentation for AR-005 and AR-014. I'll append the AR-017 design to this file.","time":{"start":1775861469436,"end":1775861469436}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775861519657,"sessionID":"ses_2866926a4ffeNtgxusNCl20XGx","part":{"id":"prt_d799790fe0014rvHer4a0sms1P","messageID":"msg_d79977dbc001HPUkan2NSsP0sm","sessionID":"ses_2866926a4ffeNtgxusNCl20XGx","type":"tool","tool":"edit","callID":"toolu_7fe122a9a4154b489fdf12de","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/design.md","oldString":"Uses `k8s.io/code-generator` v0.34.1 with `--with-watch` flag.","newString":"Uses `k8s.io/code-generator` v0.34.1 with `--with-watch` flag.\n\n---\n\n# Design: AR-017 PicoD JWT Middleware\n\n## Overview\n\nThis document describes the technical implementation of JWT authentication middleware for the PicoD HTTP server. The middleware validates JWT tokens on incoming requests and injects validated claims into the request context for downstream handlers.\n\n## Architecture\n\n### Component Placement\n\n```\n┌─────────────┐     ┌──────────────┐     ┌─────────────┐     ┌─────────────┐\n│   Client    │────▶│  PicoD HTTP  │────▶│ JWT Middle- │────▶│   Handler   │\n│  (with JWT) │     │   Server     │     │   ware      │     │  (Business) │\n└─────────────┘     └──────────────┘     └─────────────┘     └─────────────┘\n```\n\n### Package Structure\n\n```\npkg/picod/\n├── jwt/\n│   ├── middleware.go      # HTTP middleware handler\n│   ├── validator.go       # JWT validation logic\n│   ├── claims.go          # Custom claims structure\n│   ├── config.go          # Configuration types\n│   └── error.go           # Error types\n├── server.go              # PicoD server integration\n└── ...\n```\n\n### Dependencies\n\n- `github.com/golang-jwt/jwt/v5` - JWT parsing and validation\n- Standard library: `net/http`, `context`, `errors`, `fmt`, `strings`\n\n## Data Structures\n\n### Config\n\n```go\ntype Config struct {\n    // SigningKey is the secret key for HMAC verification\n    SigningKey []byte\n    \n    // SigningMethod is the signing algorithm (default: \"HS256\")\n    SigningMethod string\n    \n    // SkipPaths are paths that bypass JWT validation\n    SkipPaths map[string]bool\n    \n    // TokenLookup defines where to extract token from\n    // Format: \"header:<name>\" or \"query:<name>\"\n    TokenLookup string\n    \n    // ContextKey is the key to store claims in context\n    ContextKey string\n    \n    // ExpiryMax is the maximum allowed token expiry duration\n    ExpiryMax time.Duration\n}\n```\n\n### Claims\n\n```go\ntype Claims struct {\n    jwt.RegisteredClaims\n    \n    // Custom claims\n    UserID    string   `json:\"user_id,omitempty\"`\n    Namespace string   `json:\"namespace,omitempty\"`\n    Roles     []string `json:\"roles,omitempty\"`\n}\n```\n\n### Middleware\n\n```go\ntype Middleware struct {\n    config  *Config\n    keyFunc jwt.Keyfunc\n    parser  *jwt.Parser\n}\n```\n\n### Context Keys\n\n```go\ntype contextKey string\n\nconst (\n    ClaimsKey contextKey = \"jwt_claims\"\n)\n```\n\n## API Contracts\n\n### Middleware Constructor\n\n```go\nfunc New(config Config) (*Middleware, error)\n```\n\n**Behavior**:\n1. Validate config (SigningKey required, valid SigningMethod)\n2. Set defaults (SigningMethod=\"HS256\", TokenLookup=\"header:Authorization\")\n3. Create keyFunc for HMAC verification\n4. Configure parser with allowed methods\n5. Return middleware instance or error\n\n### HTTP Handler\n\n```go\nfunc (m *Middleware) Handler(next http.Handler) http.Handler\n```\n\n**Behavior**:\n1. Check if request path is in SkipPaths\n2. Extract token from header/query per TokenLookup\n3. Parse and validate JWT\n4. On success: inject claims to context, call next handler\n5. On failure: return 401/403 with JSON error response\n\n### Context Extraction\n\n```go\nfunc GetClaims(ctx context.Context) (*Claims, bool)\n```\n\n**Behavior**:\n1. Extract claims from context using ClaimsKey\n2. Return claims and true if present, nil and false otherwise\n\n### Error Response Format\n\n```go\ntype Error struct {\n    Code    string `json:\"code\"`\n    Message string `json:\"message\"`\n}\n```\n\n**Standard Error Codes**:\n| Code | HTTP Status | Description |\n|------|-------------|-------------|\n| `JWT_MISSING` | 401 | No token provided |\n| `JWT_INVALID` | 401 | Token format/structure invalid |\n| `JWT_EXPIRED` | 401 | Token has expired |\n| `JWT_SIGNATURE_INVALID` | 401 | Signature verification failed |\n| `JWT_EXPIRY_EXCEEDED` | 401 | Token expiry exceeds maximum allowed |\n\n## Implementation Details\n\n### Token Extraction\n\n```go\nfunc (m *Middleware) extractToken(r *http.Request) (string, error) {\n    parts := strings.SplitN(m.config.TokenLookup, \":\", 2)\n    if len(parts) != 2 {\n        return \"\", errors.New(\"invalid token lookup format\")\n    }\n    \n    switch parts[0] {\n    case \"header\":\n        auth := r.Header.Get(parts[1])\n        if auth == \"\" {\n            return \"\", ErrTokenMissing\n        }\n        // Strip \"Bearer \" prefix if present\n        return strings.TrimPrefix(auth, \"Bearer \"), nil\n        \n    case \"query\":\n        token := r.URL.Query().Get(parts[1])\n        if token == \"\" {\n            return \"\", ErrTokenMissing\n        }\n        return token, nil\n        \n    default:\n        return \"\", errors.New(\"unsupported token lookup type\")\n    }\n}\n```\n\n### Validation Flow\n\n```go\nfunc (m *Middleware) validate(tokenString string) (*Claims, error) {\n    token, err := m.parser.ParseWithClaims(tokenString, &Claims{}, m.keyFunc)\n    if err != nil {\n        if errors.Is(err, jwt.ErrTokenExpired) {\n            return nil, ErrTokenExpired\n        }\n        if strings.Contains(err.Error(), \"signature\") {\n            return nil, ErrSignatureInvalid\n        }\n        return nil, ErrTokenInvalid\n    }\n    \n    claims, ok := token.Claims.(*Claims)\n    if !ok || !token.Valid {\n        return nil, ErrTokenInvalid\n    }\n    \n    // Check max expiry\n    if m.config.ExpiryMax > 0 && claims.ExpiresAt != nil {\n        if time.Until(claims.ExpiresAt.Time) > m.config.ExpiryMax {\n            return nil, ErrExpiryExceeded\n        }\n    }\n    \n    return claims, nil\n}\n```\n\n### HTTP Error Response\n\n```go\nfunc writeError(w http.ResponseWriter, statusCode int, code, message string) {\n    w.Header().Set(\"Content-Type\", \"application/json\")\n    w.WriteHeader(statusCode)\n    json.NewEncoder(w).Encode(Error{Code: code, Message: message})\n}\n```\n\n## Error Handling\n\n### Error Types\n\n```go\nvar (\n    ErrTokenMissing     = errors.New(\"jwt: token missing\")\n    ErrTokenInvalid     = errors.New(\"jwt: token invalid\")\n    ErrTokenExpired     = errors.New(\"jwt: token expired\")\n    ErrSignatureInvalid = errors.New(\"jwt: signature invalid\")\n    ErrExpiryExceeded   = errors.New(\"jwt: token expiry exceeds maximum\")\n)\n```\n\n### HTTP Response Codes\n\n| Scenario | Status | Response Body |\n|----------|--------|---------------|\n| Missing token | 401 | `{\"code\":\"JWT_MISSING\",\"message\":\"Authorization token required\"}` |\n| Invalid format | 401 | `{\"code\":\"JWT_INVALID\",\"message\":\"Invalid token format\"}` |\n| Expired token | 401 | `{\"code\":\"JWT_EXPIRED\",\"message\":\"Token has expired\"}` |\n| Bad signature | 401 | `{\"code\":\"JWT_SIGNATURE_INVALID\",\"message\":\"Invalid token signature\"}` |\n| Expiry exceeded | 401 | `{\"code\":\"JWT_EXPIRY_EXCEEDED\",\"message\":\"Token expiry exceeds maximum allowed\"}` |\n\n## Testing Strategy\n\n### Unit Tests\n\n**File**: `jwt/middleware_test.go`\n\n```go\n// Test middleware construction\n- TestNew_ValidConfig\n- TestNew_MissingSigningKey\n- TestNew_InvalidSigningMethod\n\n// Test token extraction\n- TestExtractToken_Header\n- TestExtractToken_Query\n- TestExtractToken_BearerPrefix\n- TestExtractToken_Missing\n\n// Test validation\n- TestValidateToken_ValidToken\n- TestValidateToken_ExpiredToken\n- TestValidateToken_InvalidSignature\n- TestValidateToken_MalformedToken\n- TestValidateToken_ExpiryExceeded\n\n// Test handler\n- TestMiddleware_SkipPath\n- TestMiddleware_HeaderExtraction\n- TestMiddleware_QueryExtraction\n- TestMiddleware_ContextInjection\n- TestMiddleware_UnauthorizedResponse\n```\n\n### Test Helpers\n\n**File**: `jwt/test_helpers.go`\n\n```go\n// GenerateTestToken creates a signed JWT for testing\nfunc GenerateTestToken(claims *Claims, key []byte, expiry time.Duration) (string, error)\n\n// MockHTTPHandler returns a simple handler for testing\nfunc MockHTTPHandler(statusCode int) http.HandlerFunc\n\n// NewTestRequest creates an HTTP request with optional JWT\nfunc NewTestRequest(token, path, method string) *http.Request\n```\n\n### Integration Tests\n\n**File**: `jwt/integration_test.go`\n\n```go\n// Full request flow tests\n- TestFullRequestFlow_WithValidJWT\n- TestFullRequestFlow_WithExpiredJWT\n- TestFullRequestFlow_WithoutJWT\n- TestFullRequestFlow_WithSkipPath\n- TestFullRequestFlow_CustomClaims\n```\n\n### Test Fixtures\n\n```go\nfunc newTestConfig() Config {\n    return Config{\n        SigningKey:  []byte(\"test-secret-key\"),\n        SigningMethod: \"HS256\",\n        SkipPaths:   map[string]bool{\"/health\": true, \"/public\": true},\n        TokenLookup: \"header:Authorization\",\n        ContextKey:  \"claims\",\n        ExpiryMax:   24 * time.Hour,\n    }\n}\n\nfunc newTestClaims(userID, namespace string, roles []string) *Claims {\n    return &Claims{\n        RegisteredClaims: jwt.RegisteredClaims{\n            ExpiresAt: jwt.NewNumericDate(time.Now().Add(time.Hour)),\n            IssuedAt:  jwt.NewNumericDate(time.Now()),\n            Subject:   userID,\n        },\n        UserID:    userID,\n        Namespace: namespace,\n        Roles:     roles,\n    }\n}\n```\n\n## Security Considerations\n\n1. **Key Management**: SigningKey should be loaded from environment variables or secret store, never hardcoded\n2. **Algorithm Restriction**: Explicitly set allowed signing methods in parser to prevent algorithm confusion attacks\n3. **Token Expiry**: Enforce reasonable expiry validation via ExpiryMax (default 24h)\n4. **Path Whitelisting**: Default-deny approach; only paths in SkipPaths are public\n5. **Constant-Time Comparison**: Use hmac.Equal for signature verification (handled by jwt library)\n\n## Environment Configuration\n\n| Variable | Required | Default | Description |\n|----------|----------|---------|-------------|\n| `PICOD_JWT_SIGNING_KEY` | Yes | - | Secret key for HMAC verification |\n| `PICOD_JWT_SIGNING_METHOD` | No | `HS256` | Signing algorithm (HS256, HS384, HS512) |\n| `PICOD_JWT_SKIP_PATHS` | No | - | Comma-separated list of paths to skip |\n| `PICOD_JWT_TOKEN_LOOKUP` | No | `header:Authorization` | Token extraction location |\n| `PICOD_JWT_EXPIRY_MAX` | No | `24h` | Maximum allowed token expiry duration |\n\n## File Structure\n\n```\npkg/picod/jwt/\n├── config.go          # Configuration types and defaults\n├── claims.go          # Claims structure\n├── middleware.go      # HTTP middleware implementation\n├── validator.go       # JWT validation logic\n├── error.go           # Error types and messages\n├── test_helpers.go    # Test utilities\n├── config_test.go     # Configuration tests\n├── middleware_test.go # Middleware unit tests\n└── integration_test.go # Integration tests\n```"},"output":"Edit applied successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{},"diff":"Index: /home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/design.md\n===================================================================\n--- /home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/design.md\n+++ /home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/design.md\n@@ -622,4 +622,378 @@\n make gen-client  # Runs hack/update-codegen.sh\n ```\n \n Uses `k8s.io/code-generator` v0.34.1 with `--with-watch` flag.\n+\n+---\n+\n+# Design: AR-017 PicoD JWT Middleware\n+\n+## Overview\n+\n+This document describes the technical implementation of JWT authentication middleware for the PicoD HTTP server. The middleware validates JWT tokens on incoming requests and injects validated claims into the request context for downstream handlers.\n+\n+## Architecture\n+\n+### Component Placement\n+\n+```\n+┌─────────────┐     ┌──────────────┐     ┌─────────────┐     ┌─────────────┐\n+│   Client    │────▶│  PicoD HTTP  │────▶│ JWT Middle- │────▶│   Handler   │\n+│  (with JWT) │     │   Server     │     │   ware      │     │  (Business) │\n+└─────────────┘     └──────────────┘     └─────────────┘     └─────────────┘\n+```\n+\n+### Package Structure\n+\n+```\n+pkg/picod/\n+├── jwt/\n+│   ├── middleware.go      # HTTP middleware handler\n+│   ├── validator.go       # JWT validation logic\n+│   ├── claims.go          # Custom claims structure\n+│   ├── config.go          # Configuration types\n+│   └── error.go           # Error types\n+├── server.go              # PicoD server integration\n+└── ...\n+```\n+\n+### Dependencies\n+\n+- `github.com/golang-jwt/jwt/v5` - JWT parsing and validation\n+- Standard library: `net/http`, `context`, `errors`, `fmt`, `strings`\n+\n+## Data Structures\n+\n+### Config\n+\n+```go\n+type Config struct {\n+    // SigningKey is the secret key for HMAC verification\n+    SigningKey []byte\n+    \n+    // SigningMethod is the signing algorithm (default: \"HS256\")\n+    SigningMethod string\n+    \n+    // SkipPaths are paths that bypass JWT validation\n+    SkipPaths map[string]bool\n+    \n+    // TokenLookup defines where to extract token from\n+    // Format: \"header:<name>\" or \"query:<name>\"\n+    TokenLookup string\n+    \n+    // ContextKey is the key to store claims in context\n+    ContextKey string\n+    \n+    // ExpiryMax is the maximum allowed token expiry duration\n+    ExpiryMax time.Duration\n+}\n+```\n+\n+### Claims\n+\n+```go\n+type Claims struct {\n+    jwt.RegisteredClaims\n+    \n+    // Custom claims\n+    UserID    string   `json:\"user_id,omitempty\"`\n+    Namespace string   `json:\"namespace,omitempty\"`\n+    Roles     []string `json:\"roles,omitempty\"`\n+}\n+```\n+\n+### Middleware\n+\n+```go\n+type Middleware struct {\n+    config  *Config\n+    keyFunc jwt.Keyfunc\n+    parser  *jwt.Parser\n+}\n+```\n+\n+### Context Keys\n+\n+```go\n+type contextKey string\n+\n+const (\n+    ClaimsKey contextKey = \"jwt_claims\"\n+)\n+```\n+\n+## API Contracts\n+\n+### Middleware Constructor\n+\n+```go\n+func New(config Config) (*Middleware, error)\n+```\n+\n+**Behavior**:\n+1. Validate config (SigningKey required, valid SigningMethod)\n+2. Set defaults (SigningMethod=\"HS256\", TokenLookup=\"header:Authorization\")\n+3. Create keyFunc for HMAC verification\n+4. Configure parser with allowed methods\n+5. Return middleware instance or error\n+\n+### HTTP Handler\n+\n+```go\n+func (m *Middleware) Handler(next http.Handler) http.Handler\n+```\n+\n+**Behavior**:\n+1. Check if request path is in SkipPaths\n+2. Extract token from header/query per TokenLookup\n+3. Parse and validate JWT\n+4. On success: inject claims to context, call next handler\n+5. On failure: return 401/403 with JSON error response\n+\n+### Context Extraction\n+\n+```go\n+func GetClaims(ctx context.Context) (*Claims, bool)\n+```\n+\n+**Behavior**:\n+1. Extract claims from context using ClaimsKey\n+2. Return claims and true if present, nil and false otherwise\n+\n+### Error Response Format\n+\n+```go\n+type Error struct {\n+    Code    string `json:\"code\"`\n+    Message string `json:\"message\"`\n+}\n+```\n+\n+**Standard Error Codes**:\n+| Code | HTTP Status | Description |\n+|------|-------------|-------------|\n+| `JWT_MISSING` | 401 | No token provided |\n+| `JWT_INVALID` | 401 | Token format/structure invalid |\n+| `JWT_EXPIRED` | 401 | Token has expired |\n+| `JWT_SIGNATURE_INVALID` | 401 | Signature verification failed |\n+| `JWT_EXPIRY_EXCEEDED` | 401 | Token expiry exceeds maximum allowed |\n+\n+## Implementation Details\n+\n+### Token Extraction\n+\n+```go\n+func (m *Middleware) extractToken(r *http.Request) (string, error) {\n+    parts := strings.SplitN(m.config.TokenLookup, \":\", 2)\n+    if len(parts) != 2 {\n+        return \"\", errors.New(\"invalid token lookup format\")\n+    }\n+    \n+    switch parts[0] {\n+    case \"header\":\n+        auth := r.Header.Get(parts[1])\n+        if auth == \"\" {\n+            return \"\", ErrTokenMissing\n+        }\n+        // Strip \"Bearer \" prefix if present\n+        return strings.TrimPrefix(auth, \"Bearer \"), nil\n+        \n+    case \"query\":\n+        token := r.URL.Query().Get(parts[1])\n+        if token == \"\" {\n+            return \"\", ErrTokenMissing\n+        }\n+        return token, nil\n+        \n+    default:\n+        return \"\", errors.New(\"unsupported token lookup type\")\n+    }\n+}\n+```\n+\n+### Validation Flow\n+\n+```go\n+func (m *Middleware) validate(tokenString string) (*Claims, error) {\n+    token, err := m.parser.ParseWithClaims(tokenString, &Claims{}, m.keyFunc)\n+    if err != nil {\n+        if errors.Is(err, jwt.ErrTokenExpired) {\n+            return nil, ErrTokenExpired\n+        }\n+        if strings.Contains(err.Error(), \"signature\") {\n+            return nil, ErrSignatureInvalid\n+        }\n+        return nil, ErrTokenInvalid\n+    }\n+    \n+    claims, ok := token.Claims.(*Claims)\n+    if !ok || !token.Valid {\n+        return nil, ErrTokenInvalid\n+    }\n+    \n+    // Check max expiry\n+    if m.config.ExpiryMax > 0 && claims.ExpiresAt != nil {\n+        if time.Until(claims.ExpiresAt.Time) > m.config.ExpiryMax {\n+            return nil, ErrExpiryExceeded\n+        }\n+    }\n+    \n+    return claims, nil\n+}\n+```\n+\n+### HTTP Error Response\n+\n+```go\n+func writeError(w http.ResponseWriter, statusCode int, code, message string) {\n+    w.Header().Set(\"Content-Type\", \"application/json\")\n+    w.WriteHeader(statusCode)\n+    json.NewEncoder(w).Encode(Error{Code: code, Message: message})\n+}\n+```\n+\n+## Error Handling\n+\n+### Error Types\n+\n+```go\n+var (\n+    ErrTokenMissing     = errors.New(\"jwt: token missing\")\n+    ErrTokenInvalid     = errors.New(\"jwt: token invalid\")\n+    ErrTokenExpired     = errors.New(\"jwt: token expired\")\n+    ErrSignatureInvalid = errors.New(\"jwt: signature invalid\")\n+    ErrExpiryExceeded   = errors.New(\"jwt: token expiry exceeds maximum\")\n+)\n+```\n+\n+### HTTP Response Codes\n+\n+| Scenario | Status | Response Body |\n+|----------|--------|---------------|\n+| Missing token | 401 | `{\"code\":\"JWT_MISSING\",\"message\":\"Authorization token required\"}` |\n+| Invalid format | 401 | `{\"code\":\"JWT_INVALID\",\"message\":\"Invalid token format\"}` |\n+| Expired token | 401 | `{\"code\":\"JWT_EXPIRED\",\"message\":\"Token has expired\"}` |\n+| Bad signature | 401 | `{\"code\":\"JWT_SIGNATURE_INVALID\",\"message\":\"Invalid token signature\"}` |\n+| Expiry exceeded | 401 | `{\"code\":\"JWT_EXPIRY_EXCEEDED\",\"message\":\"Token expiry exceeds maximum allowed\"}` |\n+\n+## Testing Strategy\n+\n+### Unit Tests\n+\n+**File**: `jwt/middleware_test.go`\n+\n+```go\n+// Test middleware construction\n+- TestNew_ValidConfig\n+- TestNew_MissingSigningKey\n+- TestNew_InvalidSigningMethod\n+\n+// Test token extraction\n+- TestExtractToken_Header\n+- TestExtractToken_Query\n+- TestExtractToken_BearerPrefix\n+- TestExtractToken_Missing\n+\n+// Test validation\n+- TestValidateToken_ValidToken\n+- TestValidateToken_ExpiredToken\n+- TestValidateToken_InvalidSignature\n+- TestValidateToken_MalformedToken\n+- TestValidateToken_ExpiryExceeded\n+\n+// Test handler\n+- TestMiddleware_SkipPath\n+- TestMiddleware_HeaderExtraction\n+- TestMiddleware_QueryExtraction\n+- TestMiddleware_ContextInjection\n+- TestMiddleware_UnauthorizedResponse\n+```\n+\n+### Test Helpers\n+\n+**File**: `jwt/test_helpers.go`\n+\n+```go\n+// GenerateTestToken creates a signed JWT for testing\n+func GenerateTestToken(claims *Claims, key []byte, expiry time.Duration) (string, error)\n+\n+// MockHTTPHandler returns a simple handler for testing\n+func MockHTTPHandler(statusCode int) http.HandlerFunc\n+\n+// NewTestRequest creates an HTTP request with optional JWT\n+func NewTestRequest(token, path, method string) *http.Request\n+```\n+\n+### Integration Tests\n+\n+**File**: `jwt/integration_test.go`\n+\n+```go\n+// Full request flow tests\n+- TestFullRequestFlow_WithValidJWT\n+- TestFullRequestFlow_WithExpiredJWT\n+- TestFullRequestFlow_WithoutJWT\n+- TestFullRequestFlow_WithSkipPath\n+- TestFullRequestFlow_CustomClaims\n+```\n+\n+### Test Fixtures\n+\n+```go\n+func newTestConfig() Config {\n+    return Config{\n+        SigningKey:  []byte(\"test-secret-key\"),\n+        SigningMethod: \"HS256\",\n+        SkipPaths:   map[string]bool{\"/health\": true, \"/public\": true},\n+        TokenLookup: \"header:Authorization\",\n+        ContextKey:  \"claims\",\n+        ExpiryMax:   24 * time.Hour,\n+    }\n+}\n+\n+func newTestClaims(userID, namespace string, roles []string) *Claims {\n+    return &Claims{\n+        RegisteredClaims: jwt.RegisteredClaims{\n+            ExpiresAt: jwt.NewNumericDate(time.Now().Add(time.Hour)),\n+            IssuedAt:  jwt.NewNumericDate(time.Now()),\n+            Subject:   userID,\n+        },\n+        UserID:    userID,\n+        Namespace: namespace,\n+        Roles:     roles,\n+    }\n+}\n+```\n+\n+## Security Considerations\n+\n+1. **Key Management**: SigningKey should be loaded from environment variables or secret store, never hardcoded\n+2. **Algorithm Restriction**: Explicitly set allowed signing methods in parser to prevent algorithm confusion attacks\n+3. **Token Expiry**: Enforce reasonable expiry validation via ExpiryMax (default 24h)\n+4. **Path Whitelisting**: Default-deny approach; only paths in SkipPaths are public\n+5. **Constant-Time Comparison**: Use hmac.Equal for signature verification (handled by jwt library)\n+\n+## Environment Configuration\n+\n+| Variable | Required | Default | Description |\n+|----------|----------|---------|-------------|\n+| `PICOD_JWT_SIGNING_KEY` | Yes | - | Secret key for HMAC verification |\n+| `PICOD_JWT_SIGNING_METHOD` | No | `HS256` | Signing algorithm (HS256, HS384, HS512) |\n+| `PICOD_JWT_SKIP_PATHS` | No | - | Comma-separated list of paths to skip |\n+| `PICOD_JWT_TOKEN_LOOKUP` | No | `header:Authorization` | Token extraction location |\n+| `PICOD_JWT_EXPIRY_MAX` | No | `24h` | Maximum allowed token expiry duration |\n+\n+## File Structure\n+\n+```\n+pkg/picod/jwt/\n+├── config.go          # Configuration types and defaults\n+├── claims.go          # Claims structure\n+├── middleware.go      # HTTP middleware implementation\n+├── validator.go       # JWT validation logic\n+├── error.go           # Error types and messages\n+├── test_helpers.go    # Test utilities\n+├── config_test.go     # Configuration tests\n+├── middleware_test.go # Middleware unit tests\n+└── integration_test.go # Integration tests\n+```\n","filediff":{"file":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/design.md","before":"# Design: AR-005 Sandbox Creation Processor\n\n## Overview\n\nThis document describes the technical implementation for the Sandbox processor module within `pkg/workloadmanager`. The processor handles creation and lifecycle management of sandbox environments using Kubernetes custom resources.\n\n## Architecture\n\n### Component Structure\n\n```\npkg/workloadmanager/\n├── processor/\n│   ├── sandbox_processor.go      # Main processor implementation\n│   ├── sandbox_processor_test.go # Unit tests\n│   └── interface.go              # Processor interface definition\n├── types/\n│   └── sandbox.go                # Sandbox data structures\n└── config/\n    └── sandbox_config.go         # Configuration structures\n```\n\n### Integration Points\n\n- **Client-go**: Uses generated typed client for `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1`\n- **Informers**: Watches `CodeInterpreter` and `AgentRuntime` resources\n- **Listers**: Provides cached read access to resources\n\n## Data Structures\n\n### Sandbox Processor\n\n```go\ntype SandboxProcessor struct {\n    client       runtimev1alpha1.RuntimeV1alpha1Interface\n    informer     cache.SharedIndexInformer\n    lister       runtimev1alpha1.CodeInterpreterLister\n    config       *SandboxConfig\n    eventHandler cache.ResourceEventHandlerRegistration\n}\n\ntype SandboxConfig struct {\n    DefaultNamespace     string\n    ResourceTimeout      time.Duration\n    DefaultCPURequest    string\n    DefaultMemoryRequest string\n    AllowedRuntimes      []string\n}\n```\n\n### Sandbox Context\n\n```go\ntype SandboxContext struct {\n    Name         string\n    Namespace    string\n    RuntimeType  string\n    Owner        string\n    Labels       map[string]string\n    Annotations  map[string]string\n    Resources    v1.ResourceRequirements\n}\n```\n\n## API Contracts\n\n### Processor Interface\n\n```go\ntype Processor interface {\n    Create(ctx context.Context, sandbox *SandboxContext) (*runtimev1alpha1.CodeInterpreter, error)\n    Update(ctx context.Context, sandbox *SandboxContext) (*runtimev1alpha1.CodeInterpreter, error)\n    Delete(ctx context.Context, name, namespace string) error\n    Get(ctx context.Context, name, namespace string) (*runtimev1alpha1.CodeInterpreter, error)\n    Watch(ctx context.Context, namespace string) (watch.Interface, error)\n}\n```\n\n### Create Operation\n\n**Input**: `SandboxContext` with required fields: `Name`, `Namespace`, `RuntimeType`\n\n**Output**: `*CodeInterpreter` or error\n\n**Behavior**:\n1. Validate sandbox context (required fields, allowed runtime types)\n2. Check for existing sandbox with same name\n3. Construct `CodeInterpreter` object with proper labels/annotations\n4. Apply resource quotas from config\n5. Call `client.CodeInterpreters(namespace).Create()`\n6. Return created resource or error\n\n### Update Operation\n\n**Input**: `SandboxContext` with `Name`, `Namespace`, and fields to update\n\n**Output**: `*CodeInterpreter` or error\n\n**Behavior**:\n1. Fetch existing `CodeInterpreter`\n2. Apply updates (resources, labels, annotations)\n3. Call `client.CodeInterpreters(namespace).Update()`\n4. Return updated resource\n\n### Delete Operation\n\n**Input**: `name`, `namespace`\n\n**Output**: error\n\n**Behavior**:\n1. Call `client.CodeInterpreters(namespace).Delete()`\n2. Handle `NotFound` errors gracefully\n\n## Error Handling\n\n### Error Types\n\n```go\nvar (\n    ErrSandboxNotFound     = errors.New(\"sandbox not found\")\n    ErrSandboxExists       = errors.New(\"sandbox already exists\")\n    ErrInvalidRuntime      = errors.New(\"invalid runtime type\")\n    ErrValidationFailed    = errors.New(\"sandbox validation failed\")\n    ErrCreateTimeout       = errors.New(\"sandbox creation timeout\")\n)\n```\n\n### Error Wrapping\n\nAll errors wrapped with context using `fmt.Errorf(\"context: %w\", err)`.\n\n### Retry Strategy\n\n- Transient errors: 3 retries with exponential backoff (100ms, 200ms, 400ms)\n- `TooManyRequests`: Respect `Retry-After` header\n- Permanent errors: Return immediately without retry\n\n## Testing Strategy\n\n### Unit Tests\n\n**File**: `processor/sandbox_processor_test.go`\n\n**Test Cases**:\n1. `TestCreateSandbox_Success` - Valid sandbox creation\n2. `TestCreateSandbox_InvalidRuntime` - Rejected runtime type\n3. `TestCreateSandbox_AlreadyExists` - Duplicate creation\n4. `TestUpdateSandbox_Success` - Resource update\n5. `TestDeleteSandbox_Success` - Normal deletion\n6. `TestDeleteSandbox_NotFound` - Idempotent delete\n7. `TestGetSandbox_Success` - Retrieve existing sandbox\n\n### Test Fixtures\n\n```go\nfunc newTestSandboxContext(name, runtime string) *SandboxContext {\n    return &SandboxContext{\n        Name:        name,\n        Namespace:   \"default\",\n        RuntimeType: runtime,\n        Resources: v1.ResourceRequirements{\n            Requests: v1.ResourceList{\n                v1.ResourceCPU:    resource.MustParse(\"100m\"),\n                v1.ResourceMemory: resource.MustParse(\"128Mi\"),\n            },\n        },\n    }\n}\n```\n\n### Mock Setup\n\n```go\nfunc newTestProcessor(client runtimev1alpha1.RuntimeV1alpha1Interface) *SandboxProcessor {\n    return &SandboxProcessor{\n        client: client,\n        config: &SandboxConfig{\n            DefaultNamespace: \"default\",\n            ResourceTimeout:  30 * time.Second,\n            AllowedRuntimes:  []string{\"python\", \"nodejs\", \"go\"},\n        },\n    }\n}\n```\n\n### Integration Tests\n\n**File**: `processor/sandbox_processor_integration_test.go`\n\nTests against real Kubernetes cluster (kind) using `envtest`:\n1. Full lifecycle (create → update → delete)\n2. Concurrent operations\n3. Resource quota enforcement\n\n## Implementation Notes\n\n### Resource Naming\n\nCodeInterpreter resources follow pattern: `sandbox-{owner}-{uuid}`\n\n### Labels\n\nStandard labels applied to all sandboxes:\n- `app.kubernetes.io/name: agentcube`\n- `app.kubernetes.io/component: sandbox`\n- `agentcube.volcano.sh/owner: <owner>`\n- `agentcube.volcano.sh/runtime: <runtime-type>`\n\n### Annotations\n\n- `agentcube.volcano.sh/created-at: <RFC3339>`\n- `agentcube.volcano.sh/last-updated: <RFC3339>`\n\n### Timeout Handling\n\nCreation uses context with timeout from `config.ResourceTimeout`. Watch for resource to reach `Ready` phase within timeout window.\n\n---\n\n# Design: AR-014 Valkey Storage Implementation\n\n## Overview\n\nThis document describes the technical implementation of the session store for AgentCube, supporting both Redis and Valkey backends. The store persists sandbox metadata keyed by session ID, with sorted set indexes for expiry and last-activity tracking to enable garbage collection.\n\n## Architecture\n\n```\n┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│                     Application Layer                        │\n└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n                            │\n                            ▼\n┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│                    store.Singleton                           │\n│  ┌──────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐   │\n│  │ Storage() → Store (sync.Once initialization)         │   │\n│  └──────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘   │\n└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n                            │\n            ┌───────────────┴───────────────┐\n            │ STORE_TYPE (case-insensitive) │\n            ▼                               ▼\n┌───────────────────────┐       ┌───────────────────────┐\n│    redisStore         │       │    valkeyStore        │\n│  - *redisv9.Client    │       │  - valkey.Client      │\n│  - sessionPrefix      │       │  - sessionPrefix      │\n│  - expiryIndexKey     │       │  - expiryIndexKey     │\n│  - lastActivityIndex  │       │  - lastActivityIndex  │\n└───────────────────────┘       └───────────────────────┘\n            │                               │\n            ▼                               ▼\n┌───────────────────────┐       ┌───────────────────────┐\n│   Redis Server        │       │   Valkey Server       │\n│   - session:{id}      │       │   - session:{id}      │\n│   - session:expiry    │       │   - session:expiry    │\n│   - session:last_activity│    │   - session:last_activity│\n└───────────────────────┘       └───────────────────────┘\n```\n\n## Data Structures\n\n### SandboxInfo (Primary Document)\n\n**Package:** `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/common/types`\n\n```go\ntype SandboxInfo struct {\n    Kind             string              `json:\"kind\"`\n    SandboxID        string              `json:\"sandboxId\"`\n    SandboxNamespace string              `json:\"sandboxNamespace\"`\n    Name             string              `json:\"name\"`\n    EntryPoints      []SandboxEntryPoint `json:\"entryPoints\"`\n    SessionID        string              `json:\"sessionId\"`\n    CreatedAt        time.Time           `json:\"createdAt\"`\n    ExpiresAt        time.Time           `json:\"expiresAt\"`\n    Status           string              `json:\"status\"`\n}\n\ntype SandboxEntryPoint struct {\n    Path     string `json:\"path\"`\n    Protocol string `json:\"protocol\"`\n    Endpoint string `json:\"endpoint\"`\n}\n```\n\n**Storage Format:** JSON-serialized string stored at key `session:{sessionID}`\n\n### Index Structures\n\n| Index | Type | Key | Member | Score |\n|-------|------|-----|--------|-------|\n| Expiry | Sorted Set | `session:expiry` | sessionID | `ExpiresAt.Unix()` |\n| Last Activity | Sorted Set | `session:last_activity` | sessionID | `lastActivity.Unix()` |\n\n## Store Interface Contract\n\n**Package:** `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/store`\n\n```go\ntype Store interface {\n    Ping(ctx context.Context) error\n    GetSandboxBySessionID(ctx context.Context, sessionID string) (*types.SandboxInfo, error)\n    StoreSandbox(ctx context.Context, sandboxStore *types.SandboxInfo) error\n    UpdateSandbox(ctx context.Context, sandboxStore *types.SandboxInfo) error\n    DeleteSandboxBySessionID(ctx context.Context, sessionID string) error\n    ListExpiredSandboxes(ctx context.Context, before time.Time, limit int64) ([]*types.SandboxInfo, error)\n    ListInactiveSandboxes(ctx context.Context, before time.Time, limit int64) ([]*types.SandboxInfo, error)\n    UpdateSessionLastActivity(ctx context.Context, sessionID string, at time.Time) error\n    Close() error\n}\n```\n\n### Error Handling\n\n```go\nvar ErrNotFound = errors.New(\"store: not found\")\n```\n\n| Error Condition | Error Value |\n|-----------------|-------------|\n| Key does not exist on GET | `ErrNotFound` |\n| Session missing on UpdateSessionLastActivity | `ErrNotFound` |\n| SET XX fails on UpdateSandbox (key not exists) | `key not exists` error |\n| Nil sandbox on StoreSandbox | validation error |\n| Zero ExpiresAt on StoreSandbox | validation error |\n\n## Implementation Details\n\n### Singleton Pattern (singleton.go)\n\n```go\nvar (\n    initStoreOnce = &sync.Once{}\n    provider      Store\n)\n\nfunc Storage() Store {\n    initStoreOnce.Do(initStore)\n    return provider\n}\n\nfunc initStore() error {\n    storeType := strings.ToLower(os.Getenv(\"STORE_TYPE\"))\n    if storeType == \"\" {\n        storeType = redisStoreType\n    }\n    \n    switch storeType {\n    case redisStoreType:\n        provider = newRedisStore()\n    case valkeyStoreType:\n        provider = newValkeyStore()\n    default:\n        return fmt.Errorf(\"unsupported store type: %s\", storeType)\n    }\n    return nil\n}\n```\n\n### Redis Implementation (store_redis.go)\n\n#### Connection Options\n\n```go\nfunc makeRedisOptions() (*redisv9.Options, error) {\n    redisAddr := os.Getenv(\"REDIS_ADDR\")\n    if redisAddr == \"\" {\n        return nil, errors.New(\"REDIS_ADDR is required\")\n    }\n    \n    redisPassword := os.Getenv(\"REDIS_PASSWORD\")\n    passwordRequired := true\n    if v := os.Getenv(\"REDIS_PASSWORD_REQUIRED\"); strings.ToLower(v) == \"false\" {\n        passwordRequired = false\n    }\n    \n    if passwordRequired && redisPassword == \"\" {\n        return nil, errors.New(\"REDIS_PASSWORD is required\")\n    }\n    \n    return &redisv9.Options{\n        Addr:     redisAddr,\n        Password: redisPassword,\n    }, nil\n}\n```\n\n#### Key Operations\n\n| Operation | Redis Commands | Notes |\n|-----------|----------------|-------|\n| Ping | `PING` → expect \"PONG\" | Health check |\n| GetSandboxBySessionID | `GET session:{id}` | Return `ErrNotFound` on Nil |\n| StoreSandbox | Pipeline: `SETNX`, `ZADD expiry`, `ZADD last_activity` | Atomic batch |\n| UpdateSandbox | `SET key value XX` | Only update value, not indexes |\n| DeleteSandboxBySessionID | Pipeline: `DEL`, `ZREM expiry`, `ZREM last_activity` | Full cleanup |\n| ListExpiredSandboxes | `ZRANGEBYSCORE session:expiry -inf {before.Unix} LIMIT 0 limit` + pipeline GETs | Skip missing keys |\n| ListInactiveSandboxes | `ZRANGEBYSCORE session:last_activity -inf {before.Unix} LIMIT 0 limit` + pipeline GETs | Skip missing keys |\n| UpdateSessionLastActivity | `EXISTS key` → `ZADD last_activity` | Verify key exists first |\n\n### Valkey Implementation (store_valkey.go)\n\n#### Connection Options\n\n```go\nfunc makeValkeyOptions() (*valkey.ClientOption, error) {\n    valkeyAddr := os.Getenv(\"VALKEY_ADDR\")\n    if valkeyAddr == \"\" {\n        return nil, errors.New(\"VALKEY_ADDR is required\")\n    }\n    \n    valkeyPassword := os.Getenv(\"VALKEY_PASSWORD\")\n    passwordRequired := true\n    if v := os.Getenv(\"VALKEY_PASSWORD_REQUIRED\"); strings.ToLower(v) == \"false\" {\n        passwordRequired = false\n    }\n    \n    if passwordRequired && valkeyPassword == \"\" {\n        return nil, errors.New(\"VALKEY_PASSWORD is required\")\n    }\n    \n    opt := &valkey.ClientOption{\n        InitAddress: strings.Split(valkeyAddr, \",\"),\n        Password:    valkeyPassword,\n    }\n    \n    if v := os.Getenv(\"VALKEY_DISABLE_CACHE\"); v != \"\" {\n        if disable, err := strconv.ParseBool(v); err == nil && disable {\n            opt.DisableCache = true\n        }\n    }\n    \n    if v := os.Getenv(\"VALKEY_FORCE_SINGLE\"); v != \"\" {\n        if force, err := strconv.ParseBool(v); err == nil && force {\n            opt.ForceSingleClient = true\n        }\n    }\n    \n    if opt.DisableCache || opt.ForceSingleClient {\n        klog.V(4).Infof(\"Valkey options: DisableCache=%v, ForceSingleClient=%v\", \n            opt.DisableCache, opt.ForceSingleClient)\n    }\n    \n    return opt, nil\n}\n```\n\n#### Key Operations\n\n| Operation | Valkey API | Notes |\n|-----------|------------|-------|\n| Ping | `B().Ping()` → string \"PONG\" | Health check |\n| GetSandboxBySessionID | `B().Get().Key(key)` | `IsValkeyNil` → `ErrNotFound` |\n| StoreSandbox | `DoMulti`: SETNX, ZADD expiry, ZADD last_activity | Atomic batch |\n| UpdateSandbox | `SET ... XX` | Response must be \"OK\" |\n| DeleteSandboxBySessionID | `DoMulti`: DEL, ZREM expiry, ZREM last_activity | Full cleanup |\n| ListExpiredSandboxes | `Zrangebyscore` with Min(\"-inf\"), Max(before.Unix), Limit(0, limit) | Use MGET for batch load |\n| ListInactiveSandboxes | Same on last_activity key | MGET requires same slot |\n| UpdateSessionLastActivity | `Exists` → int64 must be 1, then `Zadd` | Verify existence first |\n\n#### MGET Optimization Note\n\nThe `loadSandboxesBySessionIDs` function uses single `MGET` for batch loading. This assumes all `session:{id}` keys are in the same cluster slot, which should be ensured through deployment configuration (e.g., hash tags or single-node deployment).\n\n## Environment Configuration\n\n### Common Variables\n\n| Variable | Required | Default | Description |\n|----------|----------|---------|-------------|\n| `STORE_TYPE` | No | `redis` | Provider selection (`redis` or `valkey`), case-insensitive |\n\n### Redis-Specific Variables\n\n| Variable | Required | Default | Description |\n|----------|----------|---------|-------------|\n| `REDIS_ADDR` | Yes | - | Redis server address (host:port) |\n| `REDIS_PASSWORD` | Yes* | - | Password for authentication |\n| `REDIS_PASSWORD_REQUIRED` | No | `true` | Set to `false` to disable password requirement |\n\n\\* Required unless `REDIS_PASSWORD_REQUIRED=false` (case-insensitive)\n\n### Valkey-Specific Variables\n\n| Variable | Required | Default | Description |\n|----------|----------|---------|-------------|\n| `VALKEY_ADDR` | Yes | - | Comma-separated list of Valkey addresses |\n| `VALKEY_PASSWORD` | Yes* | - | Password for authentication |\n| `VALKEY_PASSWORD_REQUIRED` | No | `true` | Set to `false` to disable password requirement |\n| `VALKEY_DISABLE_CACHE` | No | `false` | Set to `true` to disable client-side caching |\n| `VALKEY_FORCE_SINGLE` | No | `false` | Set to `true` to force single-client mode |\n\n## API Contracts\n\n### StoreSandbox Validation\n\n```go\nfunc (s *redisStore) StoreSandbox(ctx context.Context, sandboxInfo *types.SandboxInfo) error {\n    if sandboxInfo == nil {\n        return errors.New(\"sandbox cannot be nil\")\n    }\n    if sandboxInfo.ExpiresAt.IsZero() {\n        return errors.New(\"expiresAt cannot be zero\")\n    }\n    // ... proceed with atomic pipeline\n}\n```\n\n### UpdateSandbox Semantics\n\n- **Only updates the JSON value** using `SET key value XX`\n- **Does NOT modify** expiry or last-activity sorted set entries\n- **Fails if key does not exist** (Redis: returns false; Valkey: response != \"OK\")\n\n### List Operations - Orphan Handling\n\nBoth `ListExpiredSandboxes` and `ListInactiveSandboxes` tolerate orphan ZSET entries (session IDs in the index without corresponding JSON documents):\n\n```go\n// Skip entries where GET returns nil/empty\nif result == nil || result == \"\" {\n    continue // orphan ZSET member, skip\n}\n```\n\n### UpdateSessionLastActivity Preconditions\n\n1. Session ID must be non-empty\n2. If `at` is zero time, use `time.Now()`\n3. **Verify session key exists** before ZADD\n4. Return `ErrNotFound` if key does not exist\n\n## Testing Strategy\n\n### Unit Tests\n\n**File:** `pkg/store/store_redis_test.go`, `pkg/store/store_valkey_test.go`\n\n| Test Case | Description |\n|-----------|-------------|\n| `TestPing_Success` | Verify PING returns PONG |\n| `TestGetSandboxBySessionID_NotFound` | Verify `ErrNotFound` on missing key |\n| `TestStoreSandbox_NilRejected` | Verify nil sandbox validation |\n| `TestStoreSandbox_ZeroExpiresAtRejected` | Verify zero time validation |\n| `TestStoreSandbox_Atomicity` | Verify all three commands execute or fail together |\n| `TestUpdateSandbox_MissingKey` | Verify error when key doesn't exist |\n| `TestDeleteSandboxBySessionID_FullCleanup` | Verify DEL + ZREM operations |\n| `TestListExpiredSandboxes_OrphanTolerance` | Verify missing keys are skipped |\n| `TestUpdateSessionLastActivity_MissingSession` | Verify `ErrNotFound` on missing key |\n| `TestStorage_Singleton` | Verify sync.Once behavior with concurrent calls |\n\n### Integration Tests\n\n**File:** `pkg/store/integration_test.go`\n\n| Test Case | Backend | Description |\n|-----------|---------|-------------|\n| `TestIntegration_StoreAndGet` | Redis, Valkey | Full store → get cycle |\n| `TestIntegration_ExpiryIndex` | Redis, Valkey | Verify ZSET score is correct |\n| `TestIntegration_LastActivityIndex` | Redis, Valkey | Verify activity tracking |\n| `TestIntegration_GC_ListExpired` | Redis, Valkey | Garbage collection query |\n| `TestIntegration_GC_ListInactive` | Redis, Valkey | Inactivity detection |\n| `TestIntegration_ConcurrentAccess` | Redis, Valkey | Concurrent store/update operations |\n\n### Test Fixtures\n\n```go\nfunc newTestSandbox(sessionID string, expiresAt time.Time) *types.SandboxInfo {\n    return &types.SandboxInfo{\n        Kind:             \"sandbox\",\n        SandboxID:        \"sandbox-123\",\n        SandboxNamespace: \"default\",\n        Name:             \"test-sandbox\",\n        SessionID:        sessionID,\n        CreatedAt:        time.Now(),\n        ExpiresAt:        expiresAt,\n        Status:           \"running\",\n        EntryPoints:      []types.SandboxEntryPoint{},\n    }\n}\n```\n\n## Dependencies\n\n```go\nimport (\n    // Redis client\n    \"github.com/redis/go-redis/v9\"\n    \n    // Valkey client\n    \"github.com/valkey-io/valkey-go\"\n    \n    // Logging\n    \"k8s.io/klog/v2\"\n    \n    // Internal types\n    \"github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/common/types\"\n)\n```\n\n## File Structure\n\n```\npkg/store/\n├── store.go                    # Store interface definition\n├── singleton.go                # Storage() singleton with sync.Once\n├── store_redis.go              # Redis implementation\n├── store_redis_test.go         # Redis unit tests\n├── store_valkey.go             # Valkey implementation\n├── store_valkey_test.go        # Valkey unit tests\n├── integration_test.go         # Integration tests (both backends)\n└── errors.go                   # ErrNotFound and other package errors\n```\n\n## Regeneration\n\nClient code regeneration (if Kubernetes client updates are needed):\n\n```bash\nmake gen-client  # Runs hack/update-codegen.sh\n```\n\nUses `k8s.io/code-generator` v0.34.1 with `--with-watch` flag.\n","after":"# Design: AR-005 Sandbox Creation Processor\n\n## Overview\n\nThis document describes the technical implementation for the Sandbox processor module within `pkg/workloadmanager`. The processor handles creation and lifecycle management of sandbox environments using Kubernetes custom resources.\n\n## Architecture\n\n### Component Structure\n\n```\npkg/workloadmanager/\n├── processor/\n│   ├── sandbox_processor.go      # Main processor implementation\n│   ├── sandbox_processor_test.go # Unit tests\n│   └── interface.go              # Processor interface definition\n├── types/\n│   └── sandbox.go                # Sandbox data structures\n└── config/\n    └── sandbox_config.go         # Configuration structures\n```\n\n### Integration Points\n\n- **Client-go**: Uses generated typed client for `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1`\n- **Informers**: Watches `CodeInterpreter` and `AgentRuntime` resources\n- **Listers**: Provides cached read access to resources\n\n## Data Structures\n\n### Sandbox Processor\n\n```go\ntype SandboxProcessor struct {\n    client       runtimev1alpha1.RuntimeV1alpha1Interface\n    informer     cache.SharedIndexInformer\n    lister       runtimev1alpha1.CodeInterpreterLister\n    config       *SandboxConfig\n    eventHandler cache.ResourceEventHandlerRegistration\n}\n\ntype SandboxConfig struct {\n    DefaultNamespace     string\n    ResourceTimeout      time.Duration\n    DefaultCPURequest    string\n    DefaultMemoryRequest string\n    AllowedRuntimes      []string\n}\n```\n\n### Sandbox Context\n\n```go\ntype SandboxContext struct {\n    Name         string\n    Namespace    string\n    RuntimeType  string\n    Owner        string\n    Labels       map[string]string\n    Annotations  map[string]string\n    Resources    v1.ResourceRequirements\n}\n```\n\n## API Contracts\n\n### Processor Interface\n\n```go\ntype Processor interface {\n    Create(ctx context.Context, sandbox *SandboxContext) (*runtimev1alpha1.CodeInterpreter, error)\n    Update(ctx context.Context, sandbox *SandboxContext) (*runtimev1alpha1.CodeInterpreter, error)\n    Delete(ctx context.Context, name, namespace string) error\n    Get(ctx context.Context, name, namespace string) (*runtimev1alpha1.CodeInterpreter, error)\n    Watch(ctx context.Context, namespace string) (watch.Interface, error)\n}\n```\n\n### Create Operation\n\n**Input**: `SandboxContext` with required fields: `Name`, `Namespace`, `RuntimeType`\n\n**Output**: `*CodeInterpreter` or error\n\n**Behavior**:\n1. Validate sandbox context (required fields, allowed runtime types)\n2. Check for existing sandbox with same name\n3. Construct `CodeInterpreter` object with proper labels/annotations\n4. Apply resource quotas from config\n5. Call `client.CodeInterpreters(namespace).Create()`\n6. Return created resource or error\n\n### Update Operation\n\n**Input**: `SandboxContext` with `Name`, `Namespace`, and fields to update\n\n**Output**: `*CodeInterpreter` or error\n\n**Behavior**:\n1. Fetch existing `CodeInterpreter`\n2. Apply updates (resources, labels, annotations)\n3. Call `client.CodeInterpreters(namespace).Update()`\n4. Return updated resource\n\n### Delete Operation\n\n**Input**: `name`, `namespace`\n\n**Output**: error\n\n**Behavior**:\n1. Call `client.CodeInterpreters(namespace).Delete()`\n2. Handle `NotFound` errors gracefully\n\n## Error Handling\n\n### Error Types\n\n```go\nvar (\n    ErrSandboxNotFound     = errors.New(\"sandbox not found\")\n    ErrSandboxExists       = errors.New(\"sandbox already exists\")\n    ErrInvalidRuntime      = errors.New(\"invalid runtime type\")\n    ErrValidationFailed    = errors.New(\"sandbox validation failed\")\n    ErrCreateTimeout       = errors.New(\"sandbox creation timeout\")\n)\n```\n\n### Error Wrapping\n\nAll errors wrapped with context using `fmt.Errorf(\"context: %w\", err)`.\n\n### Retry Strategy\n\n- Transient errors: 3 retries with exponential backoff (100ms, 200ms, 400ms)\n- `TooManyRequests`: Respect `Retry-After` header\n- Permanent errors: Return immediately without retry\n\n## Testing Strategy\n\n### Unit Tests\n\n**File**: `processor/sandbox_processor_test.go`\n\n**Test Cases**:\n1. `TestCreateSandbox_Success` - Valid sandbox creation\n2. `TestCreateSandbox_InvalidRuntime` - Rejected runtime type\n3. `TestCreateSandbox_AlreadyExists` - Duplicate creation\n4. `TestUpdateSandbox_Success` - Resource update\n5. `TestDeleteSandbox_Success` - Normal deletion\n6. `TestDeleteSandbox_NotFound` - Idempotent delete\n7. `TestGetSandbox_Success` - Retrieve existing sandbox\n\n### Test Fixtures\n\n```go\nfunc newTestSandboxContext(name, runtime string) *SandboxContext {\n    return &SandboxContext{\n        Name:        name,\n        Namespace:   \"default\",\n        RuntimeType: runtime,\n        Resources: v1.ResourceRequirements{\n            Requests: v1.ResourceList{\n                v1.ResourceCPU:    resource.MustParse(\"100m\"),\n                v1.ResourceMemory: resource.MustParse(\"128Mi\"),\n            },\n        },\n    }\n}\n```\n\n### Mock Setup\n\n```go\nfunc newTestProcessor(client runtimev1alpha1.RuntimeV1alpha1Interface) *SandboxProcessor {\n    return &SandboxProcessor{\n        client: client,\n        config: &SandboxConfig{\n            DefaultNamespace: \"default\",\n            ResourceTimeout:  30 * time.Second,\n            AllowedRuntimes:  []string{\"python\", \"nodejs\", \"go\"},\n        },\n    }\n}\n```\n\n### Integration Tests\n\n**File**: `processor/sandbox_processor_integration_test.go`\n\nTests against real Kubernetes cluster (kind) using `envtest`:\n1. Full lifecycle (create → update → delete)\n2. Concurrent operations\n3. Resource quota enforcement\n\n## Implementation Notes\n\n### Resource Naming\n\nCodeInterpreter resources follow pattern: `sandbox-{owner}-{uuid}`\n\n### Labels\n\nStandard labels applied to all sandboxes:\n- `app.kubernetes.io/name: agentcube`\n- `app.kubernetes.io/component: sandbox`\n- `agentcube.volcano.sh/owner: <owner>`\n- `agentcube.volcano.sh/runtime: <runtime-type>`\n\n### Annotations\n\n- `agentcube.volcano.sh/created-at: <RFC3339>`\n- `agentcube.volcano.sh/last-updated: <RFC3339>`\n\n### Timeout Handling\n\nCreation uses context with timeout from `config.ResourceTimeout`. Watch for resource to reach `Ready` phase within timeout window.\n\n---\n\n# Design: AR-014 Valkey Storage Implementation\n\n## Overview\n\nThis document describes the technical implementation of the session store for AgentCube, supporting both Redis and Valkey backends. The store persists sandbox metadata keyed by session ID, with sorted set indexes for expiry and last-activity tracking to enable garbage collection.\n\n## Architecture\n\n```\n┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│                     Application Layer                        │\n└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n                            │\n                            ▼\n┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│                    store.Singleton                           │\n│  ┌──────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐   │\n│  │ Storage() → Store (sync.Once initialization)         │   │\n│  └──────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘   │\n└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n                            │\n            ┌───────────────┴───────────────┐\n            │ STORE_TYPE (case-insensitive) │\n            ▼                               ▼\n┌───────────────────────┐       ┌───────────────────────┐\n│    redisStore         │       │    valkeyStore        │\n│  - *redisv9.Client    │       │  - valkey.Client      │\n│  - sessionPrefix      │       │  - sessionPrefix      │\n│  - expiryIndexKey     │       │  - expiryIndexKey     │\n│  - lastActivityIndex  │       │  - lastActivityIndex  │\n└───────────────────────┘       └───────────────────────┘\n            │                               │\n            ▼                               ▼\n┌───────────────────────┐       ┌───────────────────────┐\n│   Redis Server        │       │   Valkey Server       │\n│   - session:{id}      │       │   - session:{id}      │\n│   - session:expiry    │       │   - session:expiry    │\n│   - session:last_activity│    │   - session:last_activity│\n└───────────────────────┘       └───────────────────────┘\n```\n\n## Data Structures\n\n### SandboxInfo (Primary Document)\n\n**Package:** `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/common/types`\n\n```go\ntype SandboxInfo struct {\n    Kind             string              `json:\"kind\"`\n    SandboxID        string              `json:\"sandboxId\"`\n    SandboxNamespace string              `json:\"sandboxNamespace\"`\n    Name             string              `json:\"name\"`\n    EntryPoints      []SandboxEntryPoint `json:\"entryPoints\"`\n    SessionID        string              `json:\"sessionId\"`\n    CreatedAt        time.Time           `json:\"createdAt\"`\n    ExpiresAt        time.Time           `json:\"expiresAt\"`\n    Status           string              `json:\"status\"`\n}\n\ntype SandboxEntryPoint struct {\n    Path     string `json:\"path\"`\n    Protocol string `json:\"protocol\"`\n    Endpoint string `json:\"endpoint\"`\n}\n```\n\n**Storage Format:** JSON-serialized string stored at key `session:{sessionID}`\n\n### Index Structures\n\n| Index | Type | Key | Member | Score |\n|-------|------|-----|--------|-------|\n| Expiry | Sorted Set | `session:expiry` | sessionID | `ExpiresAt.Unix()` |\n| Last Activity | Sorted Set | `session:last_activity` | sessionID | `lastActivity.Unix()` |\n\n## Store Interface Contract\n\n**Package:** `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/store`\n\n```go\ntype Store interface {\n    Ping(ctx context.Context) error\n    GetSandboxBySessionID(ctx context.Context, sessionID string) (*types.SandboxInfo, error)\n    StoreSandbox(ctx context.Context, sandboxStore *types.SandboxInfo) error\n    UpdateSandbox(ctx context.Context, sandboxStore *types.SandboxInfo) error\n    DeleteSandboxBySessionID(ctx context.Context, sessionID string) error\n    ListExpiredSandboxes(ctx context.Context, before time.Time, limit int64) ([]*types.SandboxInfo, error)\n    ListInactiveSandboxes(ctx context.Context, before time.Time, limit int64) ([]*types.SandboxInfo, error)\n    UpdateSessionLastActivity(ctx context.Context, sessionID string, at time.Time) error\n    Close() error\n}\n```\n\n### Error Handling\n\n```go\nvar ErrNotFound = errors.New(\"store: not found\")\n```\n\n| Error Condition | Error Value |\n|-----------------|-------------|\n| Key does not exist on GET | `ErrNotFound` |\n| Session missing on UpdateSessionLastActivity | `ErrNotFound` |\n| SET XX fails on UpdateSandbox (key not exists) | `key not exists` error |\n| Nil sandbox on StoreSandbox | validation error |\n| Zero ExpiresAt on StoreSandbox | validation error |\n\n## Implementation Details\n\n### Singleton Pattern (singleton.go)\n\n```go\nvar (\n    initStoreOnce = &sync.Once{}\n    provider      Store\n)\n\nfunc Storage() Store {\n    initStoreOnce.Do(initStore)\n    return provider\n}\n\nfunc initStore() error {\n    storeType := strings.ToLower(os.Getenv(\"STORE_TYPE\"))\n    if storeType == \"\" {\n        storeType = redisStoreType\n    }\n    \n    switch storeType {\n    case redisStoreType:\n        provider = newRedisStore()\n    case valkeyStoreType:\n        provider = newValkeyStore()\n    default:\n        return fmt.Errorf(\"unsupported store type: %s\", storeType)\n    }\n    return nil\n}\n```\n\n### Redis Implementation (store_redis.go)\n\n#### Connection Options\n\n```go\nfunc makeRedisOptions() (*redisv9.Options, error) {\n    redisAddr := os.Getenv(\"REDIS_ADDR\")\n    if redisAddr == \"\" {\n        return nil, errors.New(\"REDIS_ADDR is required\")\n    }\n    \n    redisPassword := os.Getenv(\"REDIS_PASSWORD\")\n    passwordRequired := true\n    if v := os.Getenv(\"REDIS_PASSWORD_REQUIRED\"); strings.ToLower(v) == \"false\" {\n        passwordRequired = false\n    }\n    \n    if passwordRequired && redisPassword == \"\" {\n        return nil, errors.New(\"REDIS_PASSWORD is required\")\n    }\n    \n    return &redisv9.Options{\n        Addr:     redisAddr,\n        Password: redisPassword,\n    }, nil\n}\n```\n\n#### Key Operations\n\n| Operation | Redis Commands | Notes |\n|-----------|----------------|-------|\n| Ping | `PING` → expect \"PONG\" | Health check |\n| GetSandboxBySessionID | `GET session:{id}` | Return `ErrNotFound` on Nil |\n| StoreSandbox | Pipeline: `SETNX`, `ZADD expiry`, `ZADD last_activity` | Atomic batch |\n| UpdateSandbox | `SET key value XX` | Only update value, not indexes |\n| DeleteSandboxBySessionID | Pipeline: `DEL`, `ZREM expiry`, `ZREM last_activity` | Full cleanup |\n| ListExpiredSandboxes | `ZRANGEBYSCORE session:expiry -inf {before.Unix} LIMIT 0 limit` + pipeline GETs | Skip missing keys |\n| ListInactiveSandboxes | `ZRANGEBYSCORE session:last_activity -inf {before.Unix} LIMIT 0 limit` + pipeline GETs | Skip missing keys |\n| UpdateSessionLastActivity | `EXISTS key` → `ZADD last_activity` | Verify key exists first |\n\n### Valkey Implementation (store_valkey.go)\n\n#### Connection Options\n\n```go\nfunc makeValkeyOptions() (*valkey.ClientOption, error) {\n    valkeyAddr := os.Getenv(\"VALKEY_ADDR\")\n    if valkeyAddr == \"\" {\n        return nil, errors.New(\"VALKEY_ADDR is required\")\n    }\n    \n    valkeyPassword := os.Getenv(\"VALKEY_PASSWORD\")\n    passwordRequired := true\n    if v := os.Getenv(\"VALKEY_PASSWORD_REQUIRED\"); strings.ToLower(v) == \"false\" {\n        passwordRequired = false\n    }\n    \n    if passwordRequired && valkeyPassword == \"\" {\n        return nil, errors.New(\"VALKEY_PASSWORD is required\")\n    }\n    \n    opt := &valkey.ClientOption{\n        InitAddress: strings.Split(valkeyAddr, \",\"),\n        Password:    valkeyPassword,\n    }\n    \n    if v := os.Getenv(\"VALKEY_DISABLE_CACHE\"); v != \"\" {\n        if disable, err := strconv.ParseBool(v); err == nil && disable {\n            opt.DisableCache = true\n        }\n    }\n    \n    if v := os.Getenv(\"VALKEY_FORCE_SINGLE\"); v != \"\" {\n        if force, err := strconv.ParseBool(v); err == nil && force {\n            opt.ForceSingleClient = true\n        }\n    }\n    \n    if opt.DisableCache || opt.ForceSingleClient {\n        klog.V(4).Infof(\"Valkey options: DisableCache=%v, ForceSingleClient=%v\", \n            opt.DisableCache, opt.ForceSingleClient)\n    }\n    \n    return opt, nil\n}\n```\n\n#### Key Operations\n\n| Operation | Valkey API | Notes |\n|-----------|------------|-------|\n| Ping | `B().Ping()` → string \"PONG\" | Health check |\n| GetSandboxBySessionID | `B().Get().Key(key)` | `IsValkeyNil` → `ErrNotFound` |\n| StoreSandbox | `DoMulti`: SETNX, ZADD expiry, ZADD last_activity | Atomic batch |\n| UpdateSandbox | `SET ... XX` | Response must be \"OK\" |\n| DeleteSandboxBySessionID | `DoMulti`: DEL, ZREM expiry, ZREM last_activity | Full cleanup |\n| ListExpiredSandboxes | `Zrangebyscore` with Min(\"-inf\"), Max(before.Unix), Limit(0, limit) | Use MGET for batch load |\n| ListInactiveSandboxes | Same on last_activity key | MGET requires same slot |\n| UpdateSessionLastActivity | `Exists` → int64 must be 1, then `Zadd` | Verify existence first |\n\n#### MGET Optimization Note\n\nThe `loadSandboxesBySessionIDs` function uses single `MGET` for batch loading. This assumes all `session:{id}` keys are in the same cluster slot, which should be ensured through deployment configuration (e.g., hash tags or single-node deployment).\n\n## Environment Configuration\n\n### Common Variables\n\n| Variable | Required | Default | Description |\n|----------|----------|---------|-------------|\n| `STORE_TYPE` | No | `redis` | Provider selection (`redis` or `valkey`), case-insensitive |\n\n### Redis-Specific Variables\n\n| Variable | Required | Default | Description |\n|----------|----------|---------|-------------|\n| `REDIS_ADDR` | Yes | - | Redis server address (host:port) |\n| `REDIS_PASSWORD` | Yes* | - | Password for authentication |\n| `REDIS_PASSWORD_REQUIRED` | No | `true` | Set to `false` to disable password requirement |\n\n\\* Required unless `REDIS_PASSWORD_REQUIRED=false` (case-insensitive)\n\n### Valkey-Specific Variables\n\n| Variable | Required | Default | Description |\n|----------|----------|---------|-------------|\n| `VALKEY_ADDR` | Yes | - | Comma-separated list of Valkey addresses |\n| `VALKEY_PASSWORD` | Yes* | - | Password for authentication |\n| `VALKEY_PASSWORD_REQUIRED` | No | `true` | Set to `false` to disable password requirement |\n| `VALKEY_DISABLE_CACHE` | No | `false` | Set to `true` to disable client-side caching |\n| `VALKEY_FORCE_SINGLE` | No | `false` | Set to `true` to force single-client mode |\n\n## API Contracts\n\n### StoreSandbox Validation\n\n```go\nfunc (s *redisStore) StoreSandbox(ctx context.Context, sandboxInfo *types.SandboxInfo) error {\n    if sandboxInfo == nil {\n        return errors.New(\"sandbox cannot be nil\")\n    }\n    if sandboxInfo.ExpiresAt.IsZero() {\n        return errors.New(\"expiresAt cannot be zero\")\n    }\n    // ... proceed with atomic pipeline\n}\n```\n\n### UpdateSandbox Semantics\n\n- **Only updates the JSON value** using `SET key value XX`\n- **Does NOT modify** expiry or last-activity sorted set entries\n- **Fails if key does not exist** (Redis: returns false; Valkey: response != \"OK\")\n\n### List Operations - Orphan Handling\n\nBoth `ListExpiredSandboxes` and `ListInactiveSandboxes` tolerate orphan ZSET entries (session IDs in the index without corresponding JSON documents):\n\n```go\n// Skip entries where GET returns nil/empty\nif result == nil || result == \"\" {\n    continue // orphan ZSET member, skip\n}\n```\n\n### UpdateSessionLastActivity Preconditions\n\n1. Session ID must be non-empty\n2. If `at` is zero time, use `time.Now()`\n3. **Verify session key exists** before ZADD\n4. Return `ErrNotFound` if key does not exist\n\n## Testing Strategy\n\n### Unit Tests\n\n**File:** `pkg/store/store_redis_test.go`, `pkg/store/store_valkey_test.go`\n\n| Test Case | Description |\n|-----------|-------------|\n| `TestPing_Success` | Verify PING returns PONG |\n| `TestGetSandboxBySessionID_NotFound` | Verify `ErrNotFound` on missing key |\n| `TestStoreSandbox_NilRejected` | Verify nil sandbox validation |\n| `TestStoreSandbox_ZeroExpiresAtRejected` | Verify zero time validation |\n| `TestStoreSandbox_Atomicity` | Verify all three commands execute or fail together |\n| `TestUpdateSandbox_MissingKey` | Verify error when key doesn't exist |\n| `TestDeleteSandboxBySessionID_FullCleanup` | Verify DEL + ZREM operations |\n| `TestListExpiredSandboxes_OrphanTolerance` | Verify missing keys are skipped |\n| `TestUpdateSessionLastActivity_MissingSession` | Verify `ErrNotFound` on missing key |\n| `TestStorage_Singleton` | Verify sync.Once behavior with concurrent calls |\n\n### Integration Tests\n\n**File:** `pkg/store/integration_test.go`\n\n| Test Case | Backend | Description |\n|-----------|---------|-------------|\n| `TestIntegration_StoreAndGet` | Redis, Valkey | Full store → get cycle |\n| `TestIntegration_ExpiryIndex` | Redis, Valkey | Verify ZSET score is correct |\n| `TestIntegration_LastActivityIndex` | Redis, Valkey | Verify activity tracking |\n| `TestIntegration_GC_ListExpired` | Redis, Valkey | Garbage collection query |\n| `TestIntegration_GC_ListInactive` | Redis, Valkey | Inactivity detection |\n| `TestIntegration_ConcurrentAccess` | Redis, Valkey | Concurrent store/update operations |\n\n### Test Fixtures\n\n```go\nfunc newTestSandbox(sessionID string, expiresAt time.Time) *types.SandboxInfo {\n    return &types.SandboxInfo{\n        Kind:             \"sandbox\",\n        SandboxID:        \"sandbox-123\",\n        SandboxNamespace: \"default\",\n        Name:             \"test-sandbox\",\n        SessionID:        sessionID,\n        CreatedAt:        time.Now(),\n        ExpiresAt:        expiresAt,\n        Status:           \"running\",\n        EntryPoints:      []types.SandboxEntryPoint{},\n    }\n}\n```\n\n## Dependencies\n\n```go\nimport (\n    // Redis client\n    \"github.com/redis/go-redis/v9\"\n    \n    // Valkey client\n    \"github.com/valkey-io/valkey-go\"\n    \n    // Logging\n    \"k8s.io/klog/v2\"\n    \n    // Internal types\n    \"github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/common/types\"\n)\n```\n\n## File Structure\n\n```\npkg/store/\n├── store.go                    # Store interface definition\n├── singleton.go                # Storage() singleton with sync.Once\n├── store_redis.go              # Redis implementation\n├── store_redis_test.go         # Redis unit tests\n├── store_valkey.go             # Valkey implementation\n├── store_valkey_test.go        # Valkey unit tests\n├── integration_test.go         # Integration tests (both backends)\n└── errors.go                   # ErrNotFound and other package errors\n```\n\n## Regeneration\n\nClient code regeneration (if Kubernetes client updates are needed):\n\n```bash\nmake gen-client  # Runs hack/update-codegen.sh\n```\n\nUses `k8s.io/code-generator` v0.34.1 with `--with-watch` flag.\n\n---\n\n# Design: AR-017 PicoD JWT Middleware\n\n## Overview\n\nThis document describes the technical implementation of JWT authentication middleware for the PicoD HTTP server. The middleware validates JWT tokens on incoming requests and injects validated claims into the request context for downstream handlers.\n\n## Architecture\n\n### Component Placement\n\n```\n┌─────────────┐     ┌──────────────┐     ┌─────────────┐     ┌─────────────┐\n│   Client    │────▶│  PicoD HTTP  │────▶│ JWT Middle- │────▶│   Handler   │\n│  (with JWT) │     │   Server     │     │   ware      │     │  (Business) │\n└─────────────┘     └──────────────┘     └─────────────┘     └─────────────┘\n```\n\n### Package Structure\n\n```\npkg/picod/\n├── jwt/\n│   ├── middleware.go      # HTTP middleware handler\n│   ├── validator.go       # JWT validation logic\n│   ├── claims.go          # Custom claims structure\n│   ├── config.go          # Configuration types\n│   └── error.go           # Error types\n├── server.go              # PicoD server integration\n└── ...\n```\n\n### Dependencies\n\n- `github.com/golang-jwt/jwt/v5` - JWT parsing and validation\n- Standard library: `net/http`, `context`, `errors`, `fmt`, `strings`\n\n## Data Structures\n\n### Config\n\n```go\ntype Config struct {\n    // SigningKey is the secret key for HMAC verification\n    SigningKey []byte\n    \n    // SigningMethod is the signing algorithm (default: \"HS256\")\n    SigningMethod string\n    \n    // SkipPaths are paths that bypass JWT validation\n    SkipPaths map[string]bool\n    \n    // TokenLookup defines where to extract token from\n    // Format: \"header:<name>\" or \"query:<name>\"\n    TokenLookup string\n    \n    // ContextKey is the key to store claims in context\n    ContextKey string\n    \n    // ExpiryMax is the maximum allowed token expiry duration\n    ExpiryMax time.Duration\n}\n```\n\n### Claims\n\n```go\ntype Claims struct {\n    jwt.RegisteredClaims\n    \n    // Custom claims\n    UserID    string   `json:\"user_id,omitempty\"`\n    Namespace string   `json:\"namespace,omitempty\"`\n    Roles     []string `json:\"roles,omitempty\"`\n}\n```\n\n### Middleware\n\n```go\ntype Middleware struct {\n    config  *Config\n    keyFunc jwt.Keyfunc\n    parser  *jwt.Parser\n}\n```\n\n### Context Keys\n\n```go\ntype contextKey string\n\nconst (\n    ClaimsKey contextKey = \"jwt_claims\"\n)\n```\n\n## API Contracts\n\n### Middleware Constructor\n\n```go\nfunc New(config Config) (*Middleware, error)\n```\n\n**Behavior**:\n1. Validate config (SigningKey required, valid SigningMethod)\n2. Set defaults (SigningMethod=\"HS256\", TokenLookup=\"header:Authorization\")\n3. Create keyFunc for HMAC verification\n4. Configure parser with allowed methods\n5. Return middleware instance or error\n\n### HTTP Handler\n\n```go\nfunc (m *Middleware) Handler(next http.Handler) http.Handler\n```\n\n**Behavior**:\n1. Check if request path is in SkipPaths\n2. Extract token from header/query per TokenLookup\n3. Parse and validate JWT\n4. On success: inject claims to context, call next handler\n5. On failure: return 401/403 with JSON error response\n\n### Context Extraction\n\n```go\nfunc GetClaims(ctx context.Context) (*Claims, bool)\n```\n\n**Behavior**:\n1. Extract claims from context using ClaimsKey\n2. Return claims and true if present, nil and false otherwise\n\n### Error Response Format\n\n```go\ntype Error struct {\n    Code    string `json:\"code\"`\n    Message string `json:\"message\"`\n}\n```\n\n**Standard Error Codes**:\n| Code | HTTP Status | Description |\n|------|-------------|-------------|\n| `JWT_MISSING` | 401 | No token provided |\n| `JWT_INVALID` | 401 | Token format/structure invalid |\n| `JWT_EXPIRED` | 401 | Token has expired |\n| `JWT_SIGNATURE_INVALID` | 401 | Signature verification failed |\n| `JWT_EXPIRY_EXCEEDED` | 401 | Token expiry exceeds maximum allowed |\n\n## Implementation Details\n\n### Token Extraction\n\n```go\nfunc (m *Middleware) extractToken(r *http.Request) (string, error) {\n    parts := strings.SplitN(m.config.TokenLookup, \":\", 2)\n    if len(parts) != 2 {\n        return \"\", errors.New(\"invalid token lookup format\")\n    }\n    \n    switch parts[0] {\n    case \"header\":\n        auth := r.Header.Get(parts[1])\n        if auth == \"\" {\n            return \"\", ErrTokenMissing\n        }\n        // Strip \"Bearer \" prefix if present\n        return strings.TrimPrefix(auth, \"Bearer \"), nil\n        \n    case \"query\":\n        token := r.URL.Query().Get(parts[1])\n        if token == \"\" {\n            return \"\", ErrTokenMissing\n        }\n        return token, nil\n        \n    default:\n        return \"\", errors.New(\"unsupported token lookup type\")\n    }\n}\n```\n\n### Validation Flow\n\n```go\nfunc (m *Middleware) validate(tokenString string) (*Claims, error) {\n    token, err := m.parser.ParseWithClaims(tokenString, &Claims{}, m.keyFunc)\n    if err != nil {\n        if errors.Is(err, jwt.ErrTokenExpired) {\n            return nil, ErrTokenExpired\n        }\n        if strings.Contains(err.Error(), \"signature\") {\n            return nil, ErrSignatureInvalid\n        }\n        return nil, ErrTokenInvalid\n    }\n    \n    claims, ok := token.Claims.(*Claims)\n    if !ok || !token.Valid {\n        return nil, ErrTokenInvalid\n    }\n    \n    // Check max expiry\n    if m.config.ExpiryMax > 0 && claims.ExpiresAt != nil {\n        if time.Until(claims.ExpiresAt.Time) > m.config.ExpiryMax {\n            return nil, ErrExpiryExceeded\n        }\n    }\n    \n    return claims, nil\n}\n```\n\n### HTTP Error Response\n\n```go\nfunc writeError(w http.ResponseWriter, statusCode int, code, message string) {\n    w.Header().Set(\"Content-Type\", \"application/json\")\n    w.WriteHeader(statusCode)\n    json.NewEncoder(w).Encode(Error{Code: code, Message: message})\n}\n```\n\n## Error Handling\n\n### Error Types\n\n```go\nvar (\n    ErrTokenMissing     = errors.New(\"jwt: token missing\")\n    ErrTokenInvalid     = errors.New(\"jwt: token invalid\")\n    ErrTokenExpired     = errors.New(\"jwt: token expired\")\n    ErrSignatureInvalid = errors.New(\"jwt: signature invalid\")\n    ErrExpiryExceeded   = errors.New(\"jwt: token expiry exceeds maximum\")\n)\n```\n\n### HTTP Response Codes\n\n| Scenario | Status | Response Body |\n|----------|--------|---------------|\n| Missing token | 401 | `{\"code\":\"JWT_MISSING\",\"message\":\"Authorization token required\"}` |\n| Invalid format | 401 | `{\"code\":\"JWT_INVALID\",\"message\":\"Invalid token format\"}` |\n| Expired token | 401 | `{\"code\":\"JWT_EXPIRED\",\"message\":\"Token has expired\"}` |\n| Bad signature | 401 | `{\"code\":\"JWT_SIGNATURE_INVALID\",\"message\":\"Invalid token signature\"}` |\n| Expiry exceeded | 401 | `{\"code\":\"JWT_EXPIRY_EXCEEDED\",\"message\":\"Token expiry exceeds maximum allowed\"}` |\n\n## Testing Strategy\n\n### Unit Tests\n\n**File**: `jwt/middleware_test.go`\n\n```go\n// Test middleware construction\n- TestNew_ValidConfig\n- TestNew_MissingSigningKey\n- TestNew_InvalidSigningMethod\n\n// Test token extraction\n- TestExtractToken_Header\n- TestExtractToken_Query\n- TestExtractToken_BearerPrefix\n- TestExtractToken_Missing\n\n// Test validation\n- TestValidateToken_ValidToken\n- TestValidateToken_ExpiredToken\n- TestValidateToken_InvalidSignature\n- TestValidateToken_MalformedToken\n- TestValidateToken_ExpiryExceeded\n\n// Test handler\n- TestMiddleware_SkipPath\n- TestMiddleware_HeaderExtraction\n- TestMiddleware_QueryExtraction\n- TestMiddleware_ContextInjection\n- TestMiddleware_UnauthorizedResponse\n```\n\n### Test Helpers\n\n**File**: `jwt/test_helpers.go`\n\n```go\n// GenerateTestToken creates a signed JWT for testing\nfunc GenerateTestToken(claims *Claims, key []byte, expiry time.Duration) (string, error)\n\n// MockHTTPHandler returns a simple handler for testing\nfunc MockHTTPHandler(statusCode int) http.HandlerFunc\n\n// NewTestRequest creates an HTTP request with optional JWT\nfunc NewTestRequest(token, path, method string) *http.Request\n```\n\n### Integration Tests\n\n**File**: `jwt/integration_test.go`\n\n```go\n// Full request flow tests\n- TestFullRequestFlow_WithValidJWT\n- TestFullRequestFlow_WithExpiredJWT\n- TestFullRequestFlow_WithoutJWT\n- TestFullRequestFlow_WithSkipPath\n- TestFullRequestFlow_CustomClaims\n```\n\n### Test Fixtures\n\n```go\nfunc newTestConfig() Config {\n    return Config{\n        SigningKey:  []byte(\"test-secret-key\"),\n        SigningMethod: \"HS256\",\n        SkipPaths:   map[string]bool{\"/health\": true, \"/public\": true},\n        TokenLookup: \"header:Authorization\",\n        ContextKey:  \"claims\",\n        ExpiryMax:   24 * time.Hour,\n    }\n}\n\nfunc newTestClaims(userID, namespace string, roles []string) *Claims {\n    return &Claims{\n        RegisteredClaims: jwt.RegisteredClaims{\n            ExpiresAt: jwt.NewNumericDate(time.Now().Add(time.Hour)),\n            IssuedAt:  jwt.NewNumericDate(time.Now()),\n            Subject:   userID,\n        },\n        UserID:    userID,\n        Namespace: namespace,\n        Roles:     roles,\n    }\n}\n```\n\n## Security Considerations\n\n1. **Key Management**: SigningKey should be loaded from environment variables or secret store, never hardcoded\n2. **Algorithm Restriction**: Explicitly set allowed signing methods in parser to prevent algorithm confusion attacks\n3. **Token Expiry**: Enforce reasonable expiry validation via ExpiryMax (default 24h)\n4. **Path Whitelisting**: Default-deny approach; only paths in SkipPaths are public\n5. **Constant-Time Comparison**: Use hmac.Equal for signature verification (handled by jwt library)\n\n## Environment Configuration\n\n| Variable | Required | Default | Description |\n|----------|----------|---------|-------------|\n| `PICOD_JWT_SIGNING_KEY` | Yes | - | Secret key for HMAC verification |\n| `PICOD_JWT_SIGNING_METHOD` | No | `HS256` | Signing algorithm (HS256, HS384, HS512) |\n| `PICOD_JWT_SKIP_PATHS` | No | - | Comma-separated list of paths to skip |\n| `PICOD_JWT_TOKEN_LOOKUP` | No | `header:Authorization` | Token extraction location |\n| `PICOD_JWT_EXPIRY_MAX` | No | `24h` | Maximum allowed token expiry duration |\n\n## File Structure\n\n```\npkg/picod/jwt/\n├── config.go          # Configuration types and defaults\n├── claims.go          # Claims structure\n├── middleware.go      # HTTP middleware implementation\n├── validator.go       # JWT validation logic\n├── error.go           # Error types and messages\n├── test_helpers.go    # Test utilities\n├── config_test.go     # Configuration tests\n├── middleware_test.go # Middleware unit tests\n└── integration_test.go # Integration tests\n```\n","additions":374,"deletions":0},"truncated":false},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/design.md","time":{"start":1775861519617,"end":1775861519649}}}}
